<!-- ABSTRACT -->
<h1>Abstract</h1>
<p>This minor project develops a high-performance, web-based Battlefield Awareness System designed to provide real-time geospatial intelligence and tactical command capabilities. The project was undertaken to address the latency and high computational costs associated with traditional desktop-bound military geographic information systems (GIS). A prototype was designed using a modern React frontend architecture integrated with CesiumJS for high-fidelity 3D global terrain rendering via ESRI satellite imagery. To enhance tactical decision-making, the system incorporates four core algorithms: a Kalman Filter for GPS noise reduction, K-Means++ for automated operational sector clustering, a Min-Heap Priority Queue for zero-latency threat alert management, and A* Pathfinding for safe routing around dynamic risk zones. Testing demonstrated that the application successfully maintains 60 frames-per-second rendering during high-frequency telemetry updates while accurately smoothing sensor jitter and dynamically partitioning the operational theater. The project demonstrates that complex geospatial algorithms can be effectively deployed in a lightweight browser environment, significantly reducing the cognitive load on command personnel.</p>

